#Important Steps Before Executing the Project:

Install Python (I'm using Windows, so I installed Python for Windows).
Install Visual Studio Code (VSCode).
Install faker using pip from the VSCode terminal: pip install faker.
Install boto3 using pip from the VSCode terminal: pip install boto3.

Configure Your AWS Credentials, Open your command prompt or terminal and run the following command:
aws configure
You will be prompted to enter your AWS credentials:
AWS Access Key ID [None]: your_access_key_id
AWS Secret Access Key [None]: your_secret_access_key
Default region name [None]: us-east-1
Default output format [None]: json


Ensure you have a Lambda execution role. This role will be automatically created when you create the Lambda Function. Ensure it has necessary permissions such as AmazonKinesisFullAccess, AmazonDynamoDBFullAccess, or AdministratorAccess.
